se to the trivial representation.The first approach relies on a new family of period rings built from the torsor of deformations of the variety over a universal p-adic thickening defined by J. M. Fontaine. The second approach introduces a crystalline-type topos and replaces the notion of Higgs bundles with that of Higgs isocrystals. The authors show the compatibility of the two constructions and the compatibility of the correspondence with the natural cohomologies. The last part of the volume contains results of wider interest in p-adic Hodge theory. The reader will find a concise introduction to Faltings' theory of almost étale extensions and a chapter devoted to the Faltings topos. Though this topos is the general framework for Faltings' approach in p-adic Hodge theory, it remains relatively unexplored. The authors present a new approach based on a generalization of P. Deligne's covanishing topos.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aGeometry, Algebraic. 0aGroup theory. 0ap-adic groups. 7aMATHEMATICS / Algebra / Linear.2bisacsh  aDolbeault generalized representation.  aDolbeault module.  aDolbeault representation.  aFaltings cohomology.  aFaltings extension.  aFaltings ringed topos.  aFaltings site.  aFaltings topos.  aGalois cohomology.  aGerd Faltings.  aHiggs bundle.  aHiggs bundles.  aHiggs crystals.  aHiggs envelopes.  aHiggs isocrystal.  aHiggsДate algebra.  aHodgeДate representation.  aHodgeДate structure.  aHodgeДate theory.  aHyodo's theory.  aKoszul complex.  aadditive categories.  aadic module.  aalmost faithfully flat descent.  aalmost faithfully flat module.  aalmost flat module.  aalmost isomorphism.  aalmost tale covering.  aalmost tale extension.  acohomology.  acovanishing topos.  acrystalline-type topos.  adeformation.  adiscrete A